						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Fragment lying in the temple of Gaḷagēśvara.</hi></p>						

						<p>Sōmēśvara I—A.D. 1055-56.</p>						

						<p>This fragmentary inscription refers itself to the reign of <hi rend="bold">Trailōkyamalla</hi> and is <hi rend="bold">dated in Śaka 977</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1055-56.</hi> The other details of the date are lost.</p>						

						<p>A <hi rend="italic">Mahāmaṇḍalēśvara</hi> (name lost) of the <hi rend="bold">Kadamba</hi> family is mentioned.</p>						

						</summary>
